WEBVTT

00:04.418 --> 00:08.192
(<i>dance music playing</i>)

00:08.292 --> 00:14.499
(<i>indistinct conversations</i>)

00:20.834 --> 00:22.067
I knew you'd come back.

00:22.167 --> 00:23.775
Piper...
Phoebe was worried,

00:23.875 --> 00:24.567
Prue was a wreck,

00:24.667 --> 00:26.399
but I knew you'd find a way.

00:26.499 --> 00:27.276
We need to talk.

00:27.376 --> 00:29.525
Leo, you haven't
kissed me in over a week.

00:29.625 --> 00:32.418
Don't you think
maybe that takes priority?

00:42.292 --> 00:44.734
I came to say good-bye.

00:44.834 --> 00:45.442
What?

00:45.542 --> 00:46.483
They told us
to break up

00:46.583 --> 00:48.442
when they caught us trying
to get married.

00:48.542 --> 00:51.859
So, uh, we won't
get married, we'll wait.

00:51.959 --> 00:53.276
It's too late;
we broke the rules.

00:53.376 --> 00:55.775
(<i>echoing</i>):
Now they won't let us
see each other again.

00:55.875 --> 01:00.399
(<i>echoing</i>):
Wait a minute-- they won't what?

01:00.499 --> 01:01.901
I don't care what they do to me,

01:02.001 --> 01:03.692
but I couldn't bear
anything happening to you.

01:03.792 --> 01:06.775
(<i>fading</i>):
I shouldn't
even be here right now.

01:06.875 --> 01:09.399
Wait, Leo, I can't hear you.

01:09.499 --> 01:10.399
What are you saying?

01:10.499 --> 01:13.625
(<i>faint</i>):
You have to forget about me.

01:15.542 --> 01:17.692
No...

01:17.792 --> 01:21.167
(<i>mouthing</i>)

01:24.251 --> 01:25.500
Leo!

01:26.750 --> 01:30.984
(<i>Piper gasping, dance music
 throbbing distantly</i>)

01:31.084 --> 01:33.499
(<i>echoing</i>):
Leo!

01:35.499 --> 01:36.734
(<i>echoing</i>):
Piper!

01:36.834 --> 01:39.359
Piper!

01:39.459 --> 01:41.334
Piper, wake up!

01:42.459 --> 01:46.084
Piper!
(<i>gasping</i>)

01:48.583 --> 01:51.917
Leo's not coming back.

01:52.959 --> 01:56.483
Honey, it was just a bad dream.

01:56.583 --> 01:58.276
No, it wasn't.

01:58.376 --> 01:59.817
It was real.

01:59.917 --> 02:04.399
(<i>crying</i>):
I don't understand.

02:04.499 --> 02:06.399
Why are they
doing this to us?

02:06.499 --> 02:10.901
It's like destroying lives
is how they amuse themselves.

02:11.001 --> 02:12.734
Piper, watch what you say.

02:12.834 --> 02:14.984
Why?
What are they gonna do to me?

02:15.084 --> 02:19.042
They couldn't hurt me more
than they already have.

02:27.834 --> 02:29.399
(<i>music playing</i>)

02:29.499 --> 02:32.276
(<i>cell phone ringing</i>)

02:32.376 --> 02:35.276
Don't you
just love cell phones?

02:35.376 --> 02:36.734
Hey, uh, it's me.

02:36.834 --> 02:38.399
It's amazing how much stress

02:38.499 --> 02:40.692
you can project
with so few words, Prue.

02:40.792 --> 02:43.026
I will have your
precious car home momentarily.

02:43.126 --> 02:45.400
Phoebe, I am not
calling about the car,

02:45.500 --> 02:46.609
I'm calling about Piper.

02:46.709 --> 02:50.483
Look, um, she had
this dream about Leo,

02:50.583 --> 02:51.483
and maybe I'm overreacting,

02:51.583 --> 02:53.359
but I've never
seen her like this.

02:53.459 --> 02:56.318
It's-it's like she's
completely given up.

02:56.418 --> 02:58.318
What kind
of dream about Le-- oh!!

02:58.418 --> 03:01.901
(<i>tires screeching</i>)

03:02.001 --> 03:02.442
Phoebe?

03:02.542 --> 03:03.942
I'm fine, the car's fine,

03:04.042 --> 03:06.001
I'll see you later, bye.

03:09.001 --> 03:10.359
Hi. Are you okay?

03:10.459 --> 03:12.609
You can't have it!
Leave me alone!

03:12.709 --> 03:15.499
I won't give it to you!
Leave me alone!

03:20.500 --> 03:24.499
(<i>panting</i>)

03:25.667 --> 03:27.084
(<i>grunts</i>)

03:28.042 --> 03:30.692
(<i>eerie growling</i>)

03:30.792 --> 03:32.834
(<i>screams</i>)

03:36.334 --> 03:38.276
It's okay.

03:38.376 --> 03:39.399
It's okay.

03:39.499 --> 03:41.709
You're safe. You're safe.

04:39.917 --> 04:40.942
Okay...

04:41.042 --> 04:44.399
you just have to be very careful
because it's hot,

04:44.499 --> 04:45.901
so blow on it, okay?

04:46.001 --> 04:49.192
Hey, did you find out
any more from her?

04:49.292 --> 04:50.525
Name, rank and serial number.

04:50.625 --> 04:54.525
Uh, her parents are on the way,
they live up the street.

04:54.625 --> 04:57.167
They were very worried
about you.

04:57.792 --> 05:00.775
I'm gonna go to the car
and get her jacket.

05:00.875 --> 05:02.609
Uh, keys?

05:02.709 --> 05:03.276
What?

05:03.376 --> 05:04.525
You know-- silver shiny things

05:04.625 --> 05:06.109
that go jingle, jingle?

05:06.209 --> 05:07.901
I don't have them.

05:08.001 --> 05:09.399
That's so weird.

05:09.499 --> 05:10.984
I put them up here.

05:11.084 --> 05:14.499
The fairies probably hid them.

05:15.209 --> 05:16.817
What was that?

05:16.917 --> 05:20.609
Sorry. I'm not supposed
to talk about fairies.

05:20.709 --> 05:22.692
Um, you know what?

05:22.792 --> 05:25.859
In this house, you can talk
about anything you want.

05:25.959 --> 05:29.359
Sometimes we talk
about weird things, too.

05:29.459 --> 05:32.109
Well, that's what
fairies do.

05:32.209 --> 05:34.525
Hide your keys and things.

05:34.625 --> 05:36.399
They're tricky
like that.

05:36.499 --> 05:40.483
Um, is that what's in that box?

05:40.583 --> 05:43.834
Is it a fairy?

05:44.499 --> 05:46.234
Is that who
you're protecting?

05:46.334 --> 05:48.499
(<i>doorbell chimes</i>)

05:49.625 --> 05:51.692
That's probably your
mom and your dad.

05:51.792 --> 05:53.399
He's not my dad.

05:53.499 --> 05:57.209
He's just my mom's
new husband.

05:59.834 --> 06:02.276
Hi, we're
Kate's parents.

06:02.376 --> 06:03.318
Is she all right?

06:03.418 --> 06:03.942
Yeah, she's fine.

06:04.042 --> 06:06.067
I mean, she scraped
her arm a little bit,

06:06.167 --> 06:08.399
but mostly
she's just scared.

06:08.499 --> 06:09.359
Kate?

06:09.459 --> 06:10.650
Get out of the doorway!

06:10.750 --> 06:11.399
Kate...

06:11.499 --> 06:14.418
It's an in-between,
get out of the in-between!

06:17.334 --> 06:18.067
What's an in-between?

06:18.167 --> 06:19.442
It's where the trolls are.

06:19.542 --> 06:20.109
Honey,

06:20.209 --> 06:22.525
we've had this
conversation before.

06:22.625 --> 06:24.734
You're a big girl
and it's time

06:24.834 --> 06:27.625
to stop believing
in things like that.

06:29.292 --> 06:32.026
She's had
some problems...

06:32.126 --> 06:33.942
since her father
and I divorced.

06:34.042 --> 06:36.399
Regressed,
sort of,

06:36.499 --> 06:38.399
back to the "imaginary
friend" stage.

06:38.499 --> 06:39.525
Look, uh, we...

06:39.625 --> 06:40.984
we should go;
it's late.

06:41.084 --> 06:44.859
Thank you again
for everything.

06:44.959 --> 06:46.483
They'll get us.

06:46.583 --> 06:49.399
I won't let them.

06:49.499 --> 06:52.418
It's okay.
Come on.

06:55.917 --> 06:58.625
KATE:
Look, there it is!

07:09.334 --> 07:11.276
Uh... thank you.

07:11.376 --> 07:13.418
You're welcome.

07:19.500 --> 07:20.483
Come on, Phoebe.

07:20.583 --> 07:21.775
Trolls and fairies?

07:21.875 --> 07:23.525
You don't believe that stuff.

07:23.625 --> 07:24.775
Sure, why not?

07:24.875 --> 07:28.399
Well, maybe it's time
we tell her about Santa.

07:28.499 --> 07:32.151
All I know is something
was definitely after her.

07:32.251 --> 07:33.399
But you didn't see anything.

07:33.499 --> 07:35.442
No, but how else
did she get hurt?

07:35.542 --> 07:37.109
How about
she fell down

07:37.209 --> 07:37.984
and scratched herself?

07:38.084 --> 07:39.817
No, Piper,
they weren't scratches,

07:39.917 --> 07:40.650
they were claw marks.

07:40.750 --> 07:43.817
If they were, you would have
seen what had clawed her.

07:43.917 --> 07:45.650
Why are you being
so stubborn about this?

07:45.750 --> 07:48.709
Because I'm a Scorpio.
What's your excuse?

07:49.251 --> 07:50.399
Okay.

07:50.499 --> 07:51.775
So it's kinda late and, um,

07:51.875 --> 07:52.942
we're all a little bit tired,

07:53.042 --> 07:55.318
so how about we finish
this up tomorrow?

07:55.418 --> 07:56.067
Now look what
you did.

07:56.167 --> 07:58.525
You went and turned Prue
into the middle child.

07:58.625 --> 07:59.234
Okay, Phoebe.

07:59.334 --> 08:01.234
Even if fairies
and trolls do exist,

08:01.334 --> 08:02.318
you heard what her mom said.

08:02.418 --> 08:04.525
The problem started
when her father left.

08:04.625 --> 08:06.026
That's psychology,

08:06.126 --> 08:07.276
not magic.

08:07.376 --> 08:07.942
I know.

08:08.042 --> 08:08.692
But you know what?

08:08.792 --> 08:10.692
I'm gonna check <i>The Book of
 Shadows</i> just in case.

08:10.792 --> 08:13.318
'Cause I don't want to be
out-stubborned by a Gemini.

08:13.418 --> 08:16.499
(<i>tea pot whistling</i>)

08:19.667 --> 08:22.251
Good night, sweetie.

08:27.418 --> 08:27.901
No, don't!

08:28.001 --> 08:29.151
The tweens!

08:29.251 --> 08:30.399
They come out of the shadows!

08:30.499 --> 08:35.042
Honey, just go to sleep, okay?

08:36.833 --> 08:39.625
(<i>door creaking</i>)

08:42.833 --> 08:44.500
Please...

08:45.042 --> 08:48.650
(<i>eerie voice
snickering, muttering</i>)

08:48.750 --> 08:50.151
Go away.

08:50.251 --> 08:52.399
(<i>eerie voice muttering</i>)

08:52.499 --> 08:53.792
Leave us alone.

08:54.334 --> 08:58.042
(<i>eerie muttering
 continues</i>)

09:01.209 --> 09:02.667
(<i>screams</i>)

09:04.500 --> 09:06.399
(<i>footsteps approaching</i>)

09:06.499 --> 09:08.209
PRUE:
Hey.

09:09.418 --> 09:11.399
Check this out.

09:11.499 --> 09:13.525
We each drew one.

09:13.625 --> 09:14.525
Lilly...

09:14.625 --> 09:16.399
Do you remember her?
She was our little

09:16.499 --> 09:18.399
imaginary friend we
had when we were kids.

09:18.499 --> 09:21.151
I have not thought
about Lilly in years.

09:21.251 --> 09:25.399
That's because you grew up
and you stopped seeing her.

09:25.499 --> 09:27.692
Okay...

09:27.792 --> 09:29.984
"Fairies,
elves and trolls

09:30.084 --> 09:30.787
"are mystical creatures

09:30.797 --> 09:32.775
"that live in a realm
parallel to ours,

09:32.875 --> 09:35.525
but separated by
a thin veil."

09:35.625 --> 09:38.234
<i>The Enchanted Realm?</i>

09:38.334 --> 09:41.984
"A thin veil which lifts
only in tween places."

09:42.084 --> 09:42.817
Tween places, Prue.

09:42.917 --> 09:46.026
That's like a realm
in between two things.

09:46.126 --> 09:49.567
Like doorways
and windows, um, shadows...

09:49.667 --> 09:50.318
Shadows?

09:50.418 --> 09:52.026
In between light and dark.

09:52.126 --> 09:53.399
And it's exactly
what Kate said,

09:53.499 --> 09:54.859
trolls live in the in-between.

09:54.959 --> 09:58.276
Right, but when you found Kate,
she wasn't in an in-between.

09:58.376 --> 10:00.318
Mm, actually,
she was in the biggest

10:00.418 --> 10:02.318
in-between of all-- midnight.

10:02.418 --> 10:03.901
"In the hour between
night and day,

10:04.001 --> 10:05.692
the world itself
becomes a tween."

10:05.792 --> 10:08.650
Okay, so why isn't there
anything in <i>The Book of Shadows?</i>

10:08.750 --> 10:11.942
Because <i>The Book of Shadows</i>
was written by adults,

10:12.042 --> 10:12.609
and I'm assuming

10:12.709 --> 10:16.084
that scary-looking dude
in your picture...

10:16.499 --> 10:17.234
...is a troll.

10:17.334 --> 10:20.067
So then why
is he trying to hurt Kate?

10:20.167 --> 10:22.399
I don't know.
We have to ask Kate.

10:22.499 --> 10:23.192
(<i>phone ringing</i>)

10:23.292 --> 10:25.359
And we will fill Piper in
on the way.

10:25.459 --> 10:28.026
You know, maybe we should
just do this one on our own.

10:28.126 --> 10:30.399
You know, I mean,
Piper's kind of out of it.

10:30.499 --> 10:32.399
Even more reason
to drag her along--

10:32.499 --> 10:34.859
take her mind off of Leo.

10:34.959 --> 10:37.625
PIPER:
Phoebe! Phone!

10:41.334 --> 10:43.234
It's your little
lawyer boyfriend.

10:43.334 --> 10:44.276
So there.

10:44.376 --> 10:46.400
And he is not
my boyfriend.

10:46.500 --> 10:47.775
Weird.

10:47.875 --> 10:48.483
Hello?

10:48.583 --> 10:49.984
Who's not your boyfriend?

10:50.084 --> 10:53.400
Um... the... mailman.

10:53.500 --> 10:58.483
Uh, yeah, sometimes Piper
likes to tease me because I like

10:58.583 --> 11:01.151
to get the mail... a lot.

11:01.251 --> 11:02.067
Uh, so how are you?

11:02.167 --> 11:04.734
Well, it's a beautiful morning
and I got

11:04.834 --> 11:07.026
a beautiful woman on the phone,

11:07.126 --> 11:08.775
so things could be worse.

11:08.875 --> 11:12.234
God, I sound like
Billy Appleby.

11:12.334 --> 11:14.151
What?

11:14.251 --> 11:15.399
Nothing.

11:15.499 --> 11:17.026
No, wait,
what did you just say?

11:17.126 --> 11:20.609
Billy Appleby's just this
hokey guy from this old movie

11:20.709 --> 11:23.400
I watched too many times
when I was a kid.

11:23.500 --> 11:25.400
BOTH:
<i>Kill It Before It Dies.</i>

11:25.500 --> 11:26.525
You've seen it?

11:26.625 --> 11:28.234
Once or twice.

11:28.334 --> 11:28.662
Really?

11:28.672 --> 11:32.542
Too bad it's not playing,
I'd take you to see it.

11:33.583 --> 11:36.234
Course, we could always
have dinner instead.

11:36.334 --> 11:39.109
Are you asking me out,
counselor?

11:39.209 --> 11:40.499
Guilty.

11:43.084 --> 11:44.399
How about tonight?

11:44.499 --> 11:46.067
I could stop by your place.

11:46.167 --> 11:47.318
PHOEBE:
Uh, really?

11:47.418 --> 11:48.399
Uh, well.

11:48.499 --> 11:49.650
Um...

11:49.750 --> 11:50.859
Um, actually,
tonight's not good

11:50.959 --> 11:53.109
because Piper is going
through something.

11:53.209 --> 11:53.662
But I will call you

11:53.672 --> 11:56.525
and-and maybe we could
meet at the club, okay?

11:56.625 --> 11:57.399
Oh, sorry, bye.

11:57.499 --> 11:59.251
(<i>line clicks, dial tone</i>)

12:09.499 --> 12:12.334
(<i>running footsteps
 approaching</i>)

12:12.500 --> 12:14.525
Did you not look
at those drawings?

12:14.625 --> 12:16.192
They're cute, yes.

12:16.292 --> 12:17.399
Cute... Cute?

12:17.499 --> 12:20.400
We all had the same
invisible fairy friend, Piper.

12:20.500 --> 12:23.234
That is proof
that fairies exist.

12:23.334 --> 12:25.209
Or...

12:26.499 --> 12:28.192
...it proves that one of us

12:28.292 --> 12:30.318
had a really fertile
imagination,

12:30.418 --> 12:32.775
and the other two
were really big copycats.

12:32.875 --> 12:34.400
Okay, Piper,

12:34.500 --> 12:34.984
honey,

12:35.084 --> 12:37.817
just listen to me, okay?
Um...

12:37.917 --> 12:39.525
we think that
Kate's in trouble,

12:39.625 --> 12:41.399
our kind of trouble.

12:41.499 --> 12:43.692
Okay, well, I don't.

12:43.792 --> 12:45.567
And after what they did to Leo,

12:45.667 --> 12:47.234
I'm not really
all that motivated

12:47.334 --> 12:49.399
to go dig up demons for them.

12:49.499 --> 12:50.775
Trolls.

12:50.875 --> 12:51.399
Whatever.

12:51.499 --> 12:53.234
Look, you guys can do

12:53.334 --> 12:54.109
whatever you want.

12:54.209 --> 12:56.650
But I've had it.
And I'm done.

12:56.750 --> 12:58.525
What does that mean?

12:58.625 --> 13:02.318
That means that,
um, the powers that be

13:02.418 --> 13:05.399
haven't done anything
but ruin my life, so therefore

13:05.499 --> 13:08.942
I'm not gonna do anything
for them any more, okay?

13:09.042 --> 13:10.192
I'm going now.

13:10.292 --> 13:11.692
Excuse me.

13:11.792 --> 13:13.334
I'm going now.

13:16.499 --> 13:19.499
I think she's on strike.

13:30.334 --> 13:32.251
(<i>knocking on door</i>)

13:33.418 --> 13:34.399
Kate...

13:34.499 --> 13:37.667
someone's here
to see you.

13:48.001 --> 13:49.359
PRUE:
Hey.

13:49.459 --> 13:52.609
So, um... we brought you
your jacket.

13:52.709 --> 13:53.567
We had to use

13:53.667 --> 13:55.399
the spare key to get
into the car, though.

13:55.499 --> 13:58.276
I guess the fairies
hid them after all.

13:58.376 --> 13:59.400
Told you.

13:59.500 --> 14:01.650
What are you drawing?

14:01.750 --> 14:03.775
That looks like
a very scary cave.

14:03.875 --> 14:05.667
PRUE:
You know...

14:06.750 --> 14:08.542
<i>...that</i> looks
a lot like mine.

14:09.499 --> 14:10.567
That's a fairy and a troll.

14:10.667 --> 14:12.734
My mom says I'm making them up.

14:12.834 --> 14:14.418
But I'm not.

14:15.084 --> 14:18.400
Well, we believe you, okay?

14:18.500 --> 14:19.399
We just need you
to tell us

14:19.499 --> 14:22.067
everything that you know,
so that we can help.

14:22.167 --> 14:23.442
I don't know that much.

14:23.542 --> 14:25.734
Thistle's kind of hard
to understand.

14:25.834 --> 14:28.400
Fairies don't talk
the same way people do.

14:28.500 --> 14:30.609
Thistle?

14:30.709 --> 14:31.525
I saved her.

14:31.625 --> 14:34.734
See, the fairies are the bosses
of the enchanted kingdom.

14:34.834 --> 14:37.399
But the trolls wish
they were the bosses.

14:37.499 --> 14:38.359
So they kidnapped Thistle

14:38.459 --> 14:40.399
from the king and queen
of the fairies.

14:40.499 --> 14:42.775
So Thistle is a princess?

14:42.875 --> 14:43.399
Mm-hmm.

14:43.499 --> 14:44.984
But the trolls
are gonna kill her

14:45.084 --> 14:47.442
unless her parents
hand over the kingdom.

14:47.542 --> 14:49.483
It's a miniature coup d'Ã©tat.

14:49.583 --> 14:51.483
But I found her
tied up

14:51.583 --> 14:53.399
in the cave and I saved her.

14:53.499 --> 14:54.901
That was very brave of you.

14:55.001 --> 14:58.650
But now the trolls hate me
'cause I won't give her back.

14:58.750 --> 15:02.026
Most of the times I can stay
out of the in-betweens,

15:02.126 --> 15:03.318
but at midnight...

15:03.418 --> 15:05.234
There's no place to hide.

15:05.334 --> 15:07.192
Yeah, we know.

15:07.292 --> 15:10.292
Can we see her?

15:11.084 --> 15:11.984
No,

15:12.084 --> 15:13.399
only children can see fairies.

15:13.499 --> 15:16.276
Well, I don't know if this
is gonna help at all,

15:16.376 --> 15:21.625
but Prue and I, we're very in
touch with our inner children.

15:22.750 --> 15:24.834
Can we at least try?

15:25.625 --> 15:26.234
(<i>sighs</i>)

15:26.334 --> 15:28.567
We'll have to go into
an in-between.

15:28.667 --> 15:30.692
Watch out for trolls.

15:30.792 --> 15:32.500
Okay.

15:56.499 --> 15:59.001
You can't help
if you can't see her.

16:02.959 --> 16:05.192
