to kick me while I'm down?!

28:56.209 --> 29:00.609
I had a nice normal life once,
and you took that from me.

29:00.709 --> 29:02.901
You took my boyfriend,
you took my life.

29:03.001 --> 29:09.499
The least you could do is leave
me my freaking car keys!

29:10.334 --> 29:13.234
I am a good person.
I'm a good witch.

29:13.334 --> 29:16.399
And damn it, I would have made
a great wife.

29:16.499 --> 29:20.067
And how dare you take that
from me.

29:20.167 --> 29:21.399
I deserve...

29:21.499 --> 29:22.942
No, you know what?

29:23.042 --> 29:24.442
I demand...

29:24.542 --> 29:27.359
that you send him back to me.

29:27.459 --> 29:28.942
You hear me? Right now.

29:29.042 --> 29:31.901
I'm going to stand
in this very spot

29:32.001 --> 29:35.499
until you send Leo back to me.

29:44.084 --> 29:47.276
(<i>slowly ticking</i>)

29:47.376 --> 29:48.525
She said that
she was coming, right?

29:48.625 --> 29:51.399
What, did you think I
just made that part up?

29:51.499 --> 29:52.399
No, but it is
almost 12:00,

29:52.499 --> 29:53.494
and we still have to go
over to Kate's.

29:53.504 --> 29:55.859
Well, maybe we should
do it without her;

29:55.959 --> 29:56.817
do the best we can.

29:56.917 --> 29:58.650
No. I used
the power-of-three spell.

29:58.750 --> 29:59.942
It won't work without her.

30:00.042 --> 30:00.984
Well, you can rewrite it.

30:01.084 --> 30:01.901
In six minutes?

30:02.001 --> 30:03.399
Do you have a better idea?

30:03.499 --> 30:04.984
(<i>door closing</i>)

30:05.084 --> 30:06.692
Sorry I'm late.

30:06.792 --> 30:08.734
Hey. Are you okay?

30:08.834 --> 30:10.901
I thought this wasn't about me.

30:11.001 --> 30:12.276
Well, it just...

30:12.376 --> 30:14.399
You don't really seem
like you're very open.

30:14.499 --> 30:17.359
I'm as open as I'm going to get
in the next five minutes,

30:17.459 --> 30:19.542
so let's just do the damn spell.

30:20.917 --> 30:24.734
ALL:
"In this tween time,
this darkest hour,

30:24.834 --> 30:26.399
"we call upon the sacred power.

30:26.499 --> 30:30.984
"Three together, stand alone,
command the unseen to be shown.

30:31.084 --> 30:33.399
"In innocence,
we search the skies,

30:33.499 --> 30:35.442
enchanted are
our newfound eyes."

30:35.542 --> 30:37.734
You have really got
to lay off the rhyming, Prue.

30:37.834 --> 30:42.234
All right, well, um,
let's just go ring the doorbell.

30:42.334 --> 30:43.609
Piper, you freeze
Kate's parents

30:43.709 --> 30:45.442
so that we can get
past them, okay?

30:45.542 --> 30:47.026
Fine. Whatever.

30:47.126 --> 30:48.834
"Fine. Whatever."

30:54.583 --> 30:57.234
Prue? Hello?

30:57.334 --> 30:58.399
Phoebe?

30:58.499 --> 31:00.609
Please answer me.

31:00.709 --> 31:02.499
Hello?

31:10.376 --> 31:12.834
(<i>eerie mumbling</i>)

31:14.499 --> 31:16.399
(<i>cackling</i>)

31:16.499 --> 31:18.276
Aha...

31:18.376 --> 31:19.625
Ah!

31:22.251 --> 31:23.251
(<i>growls</i>)

31:24.583 --> 31:26.917
(<i>screams</i>)

31:30.500 --> 31:31.667
No!

31:33.001 --> 31:34.109
Mommy!

31:34.209 --> 31:37.667
Oh, my God! Freeze them!

31:44.334 --> 31:47.399
Phoebe, they're taking Thistle!

31:47.499 --> 31:49.359
Okay, why couldn't
we see them?!

31:49.459 --> 31:51.192
Obviously,
the spell didn't work.

31:51.292 --> 31:52.067
(<i>Kate screams</i>)

31:52.167 --> 31:53.499
KATE:
Help!

31:54.292 --> 31:55.667
Help me!

31:58.500 --> 32:01.499
Oh, no!

32:08.709 --> 32:10.442
(<i>panting</i>)

32:10.542 --> 32:13.499
Where'd she go?

32:19.418 --> 32:20.817
There is nothing here.

32:20.917 --> 32:21.692
Well, she's got

32:21.792 --> 32:22.734
to be here somewhere.

32:22.834 --> 32:23.609
She couldn't have

32:23.709 --> 32:25.067
just disappeared.

32:25.167 --> 32:25.483
Unless

32:25.583 --> 32:27.901
the trolls turned her
into a fairy?

32:28.001 --> 32:29.859
A fairy?
Why would they do that?

32:29.959 --> 32:30.399
I have no idea.

32:30.499 --> 32:34.167
Maybe to punish her
for taking Thistle.

32:34.917 --> 32:37.734
But we have to find Kate.

32:37.834 --> 32:40.650
Okay, come on,
give me a premonition.

32:40.750 --> 32:42.192
I don't understand.

32:42.292 --> 32:44.734
I mean, why couldn't
we see the trolls?

32:44.834 --> 32:46.442
We've had spells backfire
on us before,

32:46.542 --> 32:48.109
but never the power of three.

32:48.209 --> 32:49.650
It didn't backfire.

32:49.750 --> 32:54.334
The spell didn't work
because of me.

32:55.126 --> 32:55.734
Piper.

32:55.834 --> 32:57.359
No, it's... it's true.

32:57.459 --> 32:59.399
This is all my fault.

32:59.499 --> 33:01.817
I just...

33:01.917 --> 33:02.859
I wanted to save Kate.

33:02.959 --> 33:07.151
I never meant to hurt her,
I never meant for this to...

33:07.251 --> 33:08.775
Don't blame
yourself, okay.

33:08.875 --> 33:11.567
I mean you have
every right to be angry.

33:11.667 --> 33:14.817
But not at the expense
of a little girl.

33:14.917 --> 33:16.399
I just...
I don't understand

33:16.499 --> 33:21.399
how I'm supposed to believe
in anything anymore.

33:21.499 --> 33:24.583
I just want him back, Prue.

33:26.334 --> 33:27.775
I know.

33:27.875 --> 33:30.399
But, right now, we have
to get Kate back, okay?

33:30.499 --> 33:33.399
And we're going to need
your help to do that.

33:33.499 --> 33:35.192
PHOEBE:
Damn it!
Damn it!

33:35.292 --> 33:35.650
Damn it!

33:35.750 --> 33:38.234
I don't understand
what good is this power

33:38.334 --> 33:40.276
if I can't use it
when I need it?

33:40.376 --> 33:42.026
Phoebe,
you have to focus.

33:42.126 --> 33:44.399
Oh, Prue, I am focusing,
believe me.

33:44.499 --> 33:47.151
You're too upset,
so take a deep breath,

33:47.251 --> 33:48.567
Uh, guys...
and try again.

33:48.667 --> 33:49.692
I can't levitate when I want to,

33:49.792 --> 33:51.399
I can't premonition...
Guys!

33:51.499 --> 33:52.067
What?

33:52.167 --> 33:55.583
I think the spell is working.

33:57.126 --> 33:58.234
(<i>gasps</i>)

33:58.334 --> 34:00.042
Oh.

34:05.084 --> 34:07.151
Do you see it?

34:07.251 --> 34:09.399
What's it doing?

34:09.498 --> 34:12.498
I think it wants us
to follow it.

34:35.792 --> 34:38.234
I think he got scared away.

34:38.333 --> 34:38.911
Yeah, and I can see why.

34:38.922 --> 34:40.775
This looks like the cave
from Kate's drawing.

34:40.875 --> 34:44.150
First troll I see
is in really big trouble.

34:44.251 --> 34:45.542
Let's go.

34:55.126 --> 34:58.959
(<i>indistinct chattering</i>)

35:02.875 --> 35:04.499
Troll central.

35:04.959 --> 35:07.499
(<i>cackling</i>)

35:13.292 --> 35:13.912
What are they doing?

35:13.922 --> 35:15.817
PRUE:
It looks like they're
trying to start

35:15.917 --> 35:17.359
a fire, although
I don't really think

35:17.459 --> 35:19.067
that it's for roasting
marshmallows.

35:19.167 --> 35:20.442
Kate and Thistle.

35:20.542 --> 35:24.067
(<i>growling</i>)

35:24.167 --> 35:25.109
(<i>Kate screams</i>)

35:25.209 --> 35:29.151
Oh...
(<i>Kate gasping, grunting</i>)

35:29.251 --> 35:30.318
All right, Piper, do you think

35:30.418 --> 35:32.234
that you can freeze them
from here?

35:32.334 --> 35:33.525
I can try.

35:33.625 --> 35:36.418
(<i>startled yells</i>)

35:39.583 --> 35:42.667
Piper, freeze them!
They're too fast!

35:49.750 --> 35:51.399
One down.

35:51.499 --> 35:52.875
Oh, Kate!

35:55.499 --> 35:58.625
Okay. Prue, a little help here!

36:00.625 --> 36:02.499
Whoa!

36:03.917 --> 36:05.542
(<i>grunting</i>)

36:07.292 --> 36:08.109
Piper, run.

36:08.209 --> 36:09.399
PIPER:
Run? Run where?

36:09.499 --> 36:10.734
Just run, Piper, run!

36:10.834 --> 36:13.567
Freeze the flames!

36:13.667 --> 36:16.399
PRUE:
Unfreeze, now.

36:16.499 --> 36:19.542
(<i>trolls yelling</i>)

36:20.792 --> 36:26.084
Ooh. Now, that is just the way
I like my trolls-- medium well.

36:26.499 --> 36:28.542
(<i>Phoebe chuckling</i>)

36:29.084 --> 36:31.984
PHOEBE:
Hi, here you guys go.

36:32.084 --> 36:34.609
It's okay;
there you go.

36:34.709 --> 36:36.901
Um, hey, hey,

36:37.001 --> 36:39.499
hey, you guys, wait, wait up.

36:40.500 --> 36:41.359
Thistle, don't you know

36:41.459 --> 36:43.376
how to turn Kate
back into a person?

36:44.376 --> 36:46.859
PHOEBE:
Kate, you know,

36:46.959 --> 36:47.859
you can't stay a fairy,

36:47.959 --> 36:51.667
because if you do,
your mom will be very sad.

36:55.084 --> 36:57.318
Um...

36:57.418 --> 36:58.276
You know what?

36:58.376 --> 37:01.109
I think I kind of know
how you're feeling.

37:01.209 --> 37:04.734
When someone you love goes away,
it doesn't make any sense,

37:04.834 --> 37:06.817
and you feel
like the whole world

37:06.917 --> 37:07.859
is out to get you.

37:07.959 --> 37:09.400
But you know what?

37:09.500 --> 37:12.483
Your mom and dad didn't split up
to hurt you.

37:12.583 --> 37:16.151
Things just happen--
things that you

37:16.251 --> 37:18.109
may never understand,

37:18.209 --> 37:21.442
but you just have to believe
that it's for the best,

37:21.542 --> 37:25.042
even if it doesn't
always seem that way.

37:27.376 --> 37:31.334
You remember how sad you were
when your daddy left?

37:32.334 --> 37:35.399
Well, that's how sad
everybody's going to be

37:35.499 --> 37:37.499
if you don't come home.

37:57.499 --> 37:59.709
Nicely done.

38:09.667 --> 38:10.734
Ow.

38:10.834 --> 38:11.817
Yep.

38:11.917 --> 38:13.151
Ice?

38:13.251 --> 38:14.399
Bed.

38:14.499 --> 38:17.499
(<i>doorbell rings</i>)

38:24.834 --> 38:27.750
Who delivers at this hour?

38:32.959 --> 38:35.399
I think that this
is someone's way

38:35.499 --> 38:37.399
of saying thank you.

38:37.499 --> 38:38.817
Oh... here.

38:38.917 --> 38:40.692
(<i>chuckling</i>)

38:40.792 --> 38:44.067
Well, you're welcome.

38:44.167 --> 38:46.459
Oh, they're so pretty.

38:54.001 --> 38:57.334
Piper, uh, we...

38:58.292 --> 38:59.901
We, um...

39:00.001 --> 39:01.942
we just...
I know.

39:02.042 --> 39:03.399
PIPER:
It's okay.

39:03.499 --> 39:05.109
I'm actually
beginning to understand

39:05.209 --> 39:08.026
why they don't want witches
and whitelighters

39:08.126 --> 39:09.583
to be together.

39:13.917 --> 39:19.442
Marriage is, um, hard enough,
you know?

39:19.542 --> 39:25.399
But marriage
to a whitelighter...

39:25.499 --> 39:29.234
He's got to orb out
at all times of the night,

39:29.334 --> 39:33.167
and sometimes he's gone
for weeks at a time.

39:33.834 --> 39:37.400
But honestly, if I'm going
to have a meltdown

39:37.500 --> 39:40.483
every time I have no idea
where he is...

39:40.583 --> 39:44.399
then none of us are going
to be able to do our jobs.

39:44.499 --> 39:45.399
And if we had lost

39:45.499 --> 39:48.026
that little girl tonight...

39:48.126 --> 39:50.109
But we didn't.

39:50.209 --> 39:52.959
But we could have.

39:53.792 --> 39:58.499
I don't think
I could live with that.

39:59.084 --> 40:04.859
If that means
that I have to give up Leo...

40:04.959 --> 40:09.875
then I guess that's a sacrifice
I'm willing to make.

40:30.209 --> 40:32.318
Am I dreaming?

40:32.418 --> 40:34.499
No.

40:37.709 --> 40:42.126
I had a dream
that you weren't coming back.

40:45.750 --> 40:48.318
That wasn't a dream either,
was it?

40:48.418 --> 40:50.500
No, it wasn't.

40:51.209 --> 40:54.318
They had forbidden me
from ever seeing you again.

40:54.418 --> 40:56.817
LEO:
But now, I...

40:56.917 --> 40:59.399
I don't know
what you said or did,

40:59.499 --> 41:02.483
but they said
you show great courage

41:02.583 --> 41:03.399
and great faith.

41:03.499 --> 41:05.026
Enough to make them
reconsider.

41:05.126 --> 41:09.318
PHOEBE:
Does that mean you guys
could get married now?

41:09.418 --> 41:12.026
Oh...!
What? I want to know.

41:12.126 --> 41:14.399
Uh, not yet.

41:14.499 --> 41:15.359
It means they're giving us

41:15.459 --> 41:17.276
a chance to prove
we can make it work.

41:17.376 --> 41:18.650
PHOEBE:
What do you mean,

41:18.750 --> 41:20.167
like probation?

41:20.583 --> 41:22.276
LEO:
Well, if we
can show them

41:22.376 --> 41:23.067
that our relationship

41:23.167 --> 41:25.442
won't get in the way
of our work...

41:25.542 --> 41:26.859
Then we can stay together.

41:26.959 --> 41:28.734
Right,
but if anything goes wrong--

41:28.834 --> 41:30.399
if we're distracted
by each other

41:30.499 --> 41:32.901
to the detriment
of a single innocent...

41:33.001 --> 41:35.459
We won't be.

41:45.625 --> 41:47.399
Are you worried?

41:47.499 --> 41:49.399
When are you going to learn?

41:49.499 --> 41:50.399
I'm always worried.

41:50.499 --> 41:52.609
I'm relieved that
he's back, though.

41:52.709 --> 41:54.734
I mean,
not only for Piper, but...

41:54.834 --> 41:55.359
I know.

41:55.459 --> 41:57.775
Unknown, unattractive demon
on the loose.

41:57.875 --> 41:59.734
Yeah, let's not tell them
till tomorrow.

41:59.834 --> 42:00.984
I think that
the least

42:01.084 --> 42:02.483
that they deserve is one night

42:02.583 --> 42:04.567
of worry-free romance,
don't you?

42:04.667 --> 42:07.109
Mmm... romance...

42:07.209 --> 42:08.775
(<i>groaning</i>)

42:08.875 --> 42:10.234
(<i>chuckling</i>)

42:10.334 --> 42:14.026
(<i>phone ringing</i>)

42:14.126 --> 42:15.192
Turner.

42:15.292 --> 42:16.400
(<i>gasping</i>)

42:16.500 --> 42:17.399
Uh, hi, Cole.

42:17.499 --> 42:20.318
What are you, what are you doing
in the office

42:20.418 --> 42:21.483
at, uh, 2:00 in the morning?

42:21.583 --> 42:23.442
What are you doing
calling my office

42:23.542 --> 42:24.442
at 2:00 in the morning?

42:24.542 --> 42:28.859
Um, I-I was just going
to leave you a message.

42:28.959 --> 42:31.442
Save you the trouble
of having to talk to me.

42:31.542 --> 42:34.399
Why would I ever
not want to talk to you?

42:34.499 --> 42:35.817
I-I-I don't know, you know,

42:35.917 --> 42:38.609
just in case you thought
I was a drunk

42:38.709 --> 42:41.026
or a lunatic,
or a drunk lunatic.

42:41.126 --> 42:42.859
I think I'm going
to go with mystery--

42:42.959 --> 42:44.525
one I'm looking forward
to figuring out.

42:44.625 --> 42:52.734
Okay. Um, I'm going to go then,
and uh, be mysterious.

42:52.834 --> 42:54.650
I'll call you.

42:54.750 --> 42:56.817
I will answer.

42:56.917 --> 42:58.442
(<i>line clicks</i>)

42:58.542 --> 43:01.084
(<i>keypad beeps</i>)

43:01.834 --> 43:07.459
Yes. Tell them
I'm getting closer.
